<text xml:lang="ta">
  <body>
    <div xml:id="PN218">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>poṉṉun tukiru muttu maṉṉiya</l>
<l>māmalai payanta kāmaru maṇiyu</l>
<l>miṭaipaṭac cēya vāyiṉun toṭaipuṇarn</l>
<l>taruvilai naṉkala mamaikkuṅ kālai</l>
<l>yoruvaḻit tōṉṟiyāṅ keṉṟuñ cāṉṟōr</l>
<l>cāṉṟōr pāla rāpa</l>
<l>cālār cālār pālarā kupavē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>Although gold, coral, pearls and the desirable </l>
<l>sapphire that was yielded by the lasting big mountain (1f.)</l>
<l>were far apart when they appeared in space, (3a-c)</l>
<l>at the time when a good ornament of rare prices is put together, (3d-4)</l>
<l>appearing in one way worthy men always (5ab)</l>
<l>are those that have a share in worthy men. (6)</l>
<l>Unworthy ones are those that have a shar in the unworthy. (7)  </l>
</lg>
    </div>
  </body>
